%T A393929 39,0,29,12,20,8,46,1,22,14,46,0,52,1,36,28,26,1,64,8,38,20,44,1,66,
%U A393929 12,64,23,32,1,102,0,32,38,59,14,72,1,58,27,67,0,121,1,40,44,64,12,90,1,98
%N A393929 a(n) is the sum of divisors of n whose decimal representation is not a substring of the decimal representation of n.
%C A393929 a(n) <= A001065(n); matches A001065 for n=1..9, diverges at n=10.
%C A393929 a(n) = 0 iff every divisor of n appears as a substring of n (e.g. n=1, 11, 13, 17, 19, 31, 41, ...); see A239058.
%C A393929 For a prime p not containing the digit '1' (see A038603), a(p) = 1, since divisor 1 is not a substring of p's decimal representation while p itself always is.
%F A393929 a(n) = Sum_{d|n} d * [str(d) is not a substring of str(n)], where [ ] is the Iverson bracket.
%e A393929 a(10) = 7: the divisors of 10 are 1, 2, 5, 10. As substrings of "10", both "1" and "10" occur, so those two divisors are excluded, leaving 2 + 5 = 7.
%o A393929 (PARI) a(n) = sumdiv(n, d, if (#strsplit(Str(n), Str(d))<2, d)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jul 19 2026
%o A393929 (Python)
%o A393929 from sympy import divisors
%o A393929 def a(n): s = str(n); return sum(d for d in divisors(n)[:-1] if not str(d) in s)
%o A393929 print([a(n) for n in range(1, 81)]) # _Michael S. Branicky_, Jul 19 2026
%Y A393929 Cf. A001065, A239058, A038603.
